   <p><gap unit="words" extent="1" reason="illegible"/><pb facs="5423968_4_1007.jpg" n="2"/><gap unit="words" extent="1" reason="illegible"/><pb facs="5423968_4_1008.jpg" n="3"/><gap unit="words" extent="1" reason="illegible"/><pb facs="5423968_4_1009.jpg" n="4"/><gap unit="words" extent="1" reason="illegible"/><pb facs="5423968_4_1010.jpg" n="5"/><gap unit="words" extent="1" reason="illegible"/><pb facs="5423968_4_1011.jpg" n="6"/>original owners. These crimes increase daily. During the first week of last year there were 656 robberies reported. This year, in Chicago, there were 963. The smaller petty larceny cases, or the number of persons injured are not included. Conditions are getting worse. Should the citizens not require from the police department a stronger enforcement of the laws, crime will be out of control. Why should the burden be shouldered by the citizenry? Why should millions be spent, if the expenditures do not bring any results? The safety of the citizen is jepardized to such an extent that he sometimes is not certain of his life. The bandit groups have grown and spread out more rapidly in the cities than the Italian bandits in the hills and forests.</p>
